text: in the beginning of winter. . .  sparkling,  crystal,  sky blue icicles shimmer in the dim,  goldenrod sun,  camel brown squirrels hibernate in a coffee brown oak tree,  caution orange wood fire burns deeply in my stone gray fireplace,  shimmering sights of winter.   during winter. . .  ''honk,  honk'' says the olive green and leather brown goose late for flying south as he soars high in the misty blue sky,  lobster red fire crackles like popcorn popping in the microwave,  calm sounds of winter.   while winter. . .  fresh chocolate cookies cool on the hard mahogany brown stove,  misty gray smoke like ashes burn,  sweet sugary hot chocolate fills my dad's coffee cup,  sweet smells of winter.   later in the winter. . .  the tiny,  wet,  fragile snowflakes fall gracefully down on my tongue giving me chills on my back under my warm,  fuzzy,  cherry red sweater,  i taste christmas dinner with the smoky burnt turkey and sweets galore placed on my family's table and much,  much,  more.  sugary tastes of winter.   at winter's end. . .  powdery,  puffy,  vanilla snow as cold as the atmosphere at the north pole,  sharp,  pointy needles on my pine tree pokes everyone that passes,  brown rough pine cones falling here and there,  fuzzy,  colorful mittens knitted to keep my hands warm like a nice toasty fire,  winter. . . my favorite season.

title: Mary and Sarah

text: if you look at the sky you will see the stars,   did you know they go farther then mars? so beautiful , so very bright with their beautiful shining light.  they sit in the sky and wait,   wait,  wait for a beautiful date with the moon.  they love the dark always, always.  you will never see them in the day,  but,  when it's night it's time  to play

title: Thank god it's fall

title: Books
author: morgan
text: books there are so many pages waiting to be written in  to fill in all the pages with dreams wonders and thoughts   a dove will carry a scroll of all the things i have written down  the dove will take it to a faraway land were it will never be seen  until i come to fetch it and reveal it to the world.
